Key Match Events: Christian Braun's poster dunk on Rudy Gobert led to a confrontation resulting in double technical fouls.
Minnesota Timberwolves closed the game on a 17-4 run to erase a 10-point deficit and win.
Nikola Jokić committed two turnovers in the final minutes that led to five points for the Timberwolves.
Nikola Jokić missed his last two shot attempts, including a three-pointer as time expired that would have tied the game.
Post-Match Reflections: Christian Braun took responsibility for halting the Nuggets' momentum with his technical foul.
Braun stated he needs to be more responsible and control himself better in such situations.
Nikola Jokić's miscues in crunch time were highlighted despite his overall strong performance.
Jamal Murray's continued struggles were noted, with poor shooting percentages.
Russell Westbrook's performance was criticized, highlighting his turnovers and poor shooting.
The Nuggets were described as a deeply flawed team despite having a superstar like Jokić.
